re gloomy. Both were pumping themselves up with gloomy violence. Gloomily, Anton said, “That’s not done, after all—going out walking with another’s bride.”

“And especially on Saturday night,” said Gustav.

A passerby, coming abreast of them, happened to glance at their faces—and could not help walking faster.

The night wind chased rustling rubbish along the fences. It was a dark and desolate part of Berlin. Far to the left of the road, above the canal, blinked scattered lights.